HEADWORD: Subdean
<hw>Sub"dean`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>sub-</ets> + <ets>dean</ets>: cf. F. <ets>sousdoyen</ets>.]</ety>
<def>An under dean; the deputy or substitute of a dean.</def>
